Chilean Stocks: Cap, Lan Airlines and Sudamericana de Vapores

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-09-22T19:49:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/chilean-stocks-cap-lan-airlines-and-sudamericana-de-vapores.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:45 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 5.5 percent, the most in six weeks, to
3,824.37. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL)  index retreated 8.6 percent to
2,068.98.  Cap SA (CAP)   slumped 8.2 percent to 15,685 pesos, its
steepest plunge since October 2008. Chile’s largest iron miner
and steel producer fell as base metals declined after a
preliminary index of China purchasing managers signaled a
contraction in factory output this month.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES CC) lost 10
percent to a record low 136.14 pesos. Latin America’s largest
container shipping company led losses among members of the IPSA
index after Santiago-based brokerage firm Larrain Vial SA
Corredora de Bolsa cut its recommendation to “sell” with a
price estimate of 121 pesos per share.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   fell 7 percent to 12,041 pesos.
Latin America’s largest airline by market value was the most
active stock today by value, with 20 billion pesos ($38 million)
changing hands, as global equities slumped after the  Federal
Reserve  signaled “significant downside risks” in the  U.S.
economy . Chile’s antitrust tribunal approved yesterday with
conditions Lan’s takeover of Brazil’s  Tam SA. (TAMM4)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
